		<div id="comment_body_64535299"><p>The data shows that crime rates of all types - violent crime and property crimes - have decreased dramatically since the 1990s.</p><p><a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2024/04/24/what-the-data-says-about-crime-in-the-us/sr_24-04-23_crime_3/" title="pewresearch.org">https://www.pewresearch.org/sh...</a> [pewresearch.org]</p><p>It seems your kneejerk reaction might be based on faulty perceptions. Police have become far *more* effective over the last 30 years, not less.</p></div>
	</div>

